  "finding": "Surface c_H is a THRESHOLD function of bulk pH, NOT linear: an acidic plateau (surface pH ~0.7-1.7) for bulk pH <= 2.35 where the H+ reservoir + cathodic field enrichment hold the surface acidic, and an alkaline plateau (surface pH ~9-10) for bulk pH >= 3.42 where ORR H+-consumption outruns bulk supply. The transition sits at bulk pH ~2.3-3.4. Hence a surface-c_H-reading consumption rate (C1) is ON only at bulk pH <= ~2.3 and OFF at >= 3.4 -> reproduces the data's ring-magnitude collapse at pH 2 and survival at pH 4/6 (mechanism C/M3). The brainstorm's bulk-limiting m (beta=1) is INVALID here: beta is ~0 on each plateau and large only across the switch, so C's apparent proton ORDER is NOT identifiable as a simple c_H^m power from bulk pH."
